President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Japan for the Tokyo 2020 Summer Olympic Games and the Closing Ceremony on August 8, 2021. The delegation will be led by Linda Thomas-Greenfield, the United States Ambassador to the United Nations. Other members of the delegation include Raymond Greene, the Chargé d’Affaires ad interim at the U.S. Embassy Tokyo, and Marcia Bernicat, the Senior Official for Economic Growth, Energy, and the Environment and Acting Assistant Secretary of State for Oceans and International Environmental and Scientific Affairs at the U.S. Department of State.